    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-12T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-12T03:00:00-05:00" n="777"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d777">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/1756: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-12T09:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 12, 1935—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 12—7:23 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>693. Your 168, October 11, 6 p.m. The British have no instructions. The German
                    and Belgian Ambassadors here have been instructed to request the Italian
                    Government to abstain from bombing the open city of Addis Ababa if all the other
                    Governments so request but as no other Governments except France have made any
                    representations they have refrained from so doing. The French have received a
                    similar instruction and the French Ambassador told the German Ambassador that he
                    felt that because of the delicate situation in which France found itself
                    vis-à-vis England and Italy he would make some mild suggestion but that it would
                    be a purely <hi rend="italic">pro forma</hi> representation and done in a very
                    casual manner.</p>
                <p>As I understand it there are no other Governments directly represented at Addis
                    Ababa.</p>
                <p>We have no information about requests concerning Diredawa.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
